      "content": "thanks for being understanding about the suppression part. it's been really hard trying to prove this to people who just call me crazy. i actually have a digital scan of a 1954 treaty between the Aethelgard council and a regional administrative body. it looks pretty official, but i need to know if there's any way to verify the legal standing of a territory that was effectively \"erased\" by a superpower. if the documents exist, what kind of formal legal process would a legitimate sovereign heir use to present these to the international community?",
