      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks for the leads. the thing is, the treaty isn't just a paper, it actually names my grandfather as the provisional regent and designates me as the successor to the throne. it's not a \"new\" state issue, it's a matter of restoring a legitimate line of succession that was interrupted. if i want to stop being just a civilian and actually start acting as the rightful head of state for the Aethelgard people, what kind of diplomatic or legal groundwork should i focus on first to make my claim undeniable?",
